Overall, 18.5% (95% CI: 16.7–21.7%) of the examined samples with valid results (n
 = 902) were positive for the PRRS EU wild-type virus by nonaplex RT-PCR. The EU genotype vaccine virus was detected in 1.3% (0.76–2.3%) and the NA genotype vaccine virus in 8.9% (6.9–11.4%) of all samples (Table 2
).
